'''Constantin Titoiu''' is a retired [[Amateur boxing|amateur boxer]] from [[Romania]]. At the [[1982 World Amateur Boxing Championships]] he won the bronze medal in the flyweight division (&ndash; 51&nbsp;kg).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/sport/boxing.htm|title=World Amateur Boxing Championships|accessdate=7 December 2010}}</ref> In the semifinals he was beaten by eventual silver medalist [[Michael Collins (boxer)|Michael Collins]] of the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://amateur-boxing.w.interia.pl/WorldChamps1982.html|title=WorldChamps1982|accessdate=7 December 2010}}</ref> He also received a bronze medal in the [[1983 European Amateur Boxing Championships]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sports123.com/box/me-51.html|title=Sports 123: Boxing: Men: Amateur European Championships: -51 kg|accessdate=7 December 2010}}</ref>

