{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Fort Maidan | nickname = | country = India | image = | location = [[Palakkad]], [[Kerala]] | establishment = 2003 | seating_capacity = 10,000 | end1 = Park End | end2 = Municipal Office End | club1 = [[Kerala cricket team]] | year1 = 2003-present | date = August 26, | year = 2015 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/columns/content/ground/58364.html Cricinfo }}
'''Fort Maidan''', also known as '''Kota Maidanam''', is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Palakkad]], [[India]]. It is currently used mostly for [[cricket]] matches. The Fort Maidan holds a maximum capacity of 10,000 peoples at a time.
Up till 2002 the ground was considered for local cricket only. In 2003, [[Ranji Trophy]] was introduced in Fort Maidan. Now Fort Maidan is a regular venue for first class cricket. Many famous state level cricket matches were held in this stadium.<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1962_f.html First-class Matches]</ref><ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1962_a.html List A]</ref>
