{{National rugby union | unionname = Entre Ríos Rugby Union | nativename = Unión Entrerriana de Rugby | logo = Union entrerriana logo.png | logosize = 120px | founded = {{Start date and age|1979}} | ground = | region = [[Argentine Rugby Union|UAR]] | regionyear = | president = Carlos Ascúa <ref>[http://www.eldiario.com.ar/diario/deportes/3981-carlos-ascua-nuevo-presidente-de-la-uer.htm "Carlos Ascúa, nuevo Presidente de la UER", ''El Diario''], 29 Apr 2011</ref> | coach = | womenscoach = | sevenscoach = | countryflag = Argentina | url = [http://uerugby.com.ar/ uerugby.com.ar] }}
The '''Entre Rios Rugby Union ''' ({{lang-es|''' Unión Entrerriana de Rugby '''}}) (also known for its initials '''UER''') is the organisational body that rules the game of [[rugby union]] in [[Entre Ríos Province]], [[Argentina]].
Best placed teams of UER qualifies to play the [[Torneo del Litoral]], along with clubs from [[Unión de Rugby de Rosario|Rosario]] and [[Unión Santafesina de Rugby|Santa Fe]] unions.
== History == The Union was founded in 1979 when the rugby clubs of [[Paraná, Entre Ríos]] decided to create their own body due to they took part of [[Unión Santafesina de Rugby]] by then. The founding members were: [[Estudiantes de Paraná]], Club La Salle, El Paraná Rowing Club and [[Club Tilcara|Tilcara]].
Other clubs then asked to be part of the union, from cities such as Diamante, La Paz, Concordia, Concepción del Uruguay, Gualeguay y Nogoyá.
== Provincial team == The Unión Entreterriana Cordobesa de Rugby is represented in the [[Campeonato Argentino]], a competition in which each of the 25 unions that make up the [[Unión Argentina de Rugby]] (UAR) participate. His best results was the final in [[1984 Campeonato Argentino de Rugby|1984 edition]]
